This is a virtual machine management system, it creates, runs, and manages virtual
machines running on a cluster of physical machines.  It currently supports DRBD and LVM
for VM storage, an has a "extstorage provider for ZFS", which is a minimal implementation
of ZFS for storing the VM discs.  I would like to implement a first-class ZFS storage
backend that in addition to all the normal functions that the LVM provider does can also
do a "live migration" by using ZFS replication.  This replication would work by taking a
snapshot, using "zfs send"/"zfs receive" to replicate that data, possibly does that one
more time to get the changes that were made while the initial bulk replication is done,
then pauses the VM, takes a final snapshot and replicates it, then live migrates the VM to
the new host.  There is a description of the code relating the the storage providers and
what might need to be done in the file "AddingStorageBackends".  Note that testing will
likely need to be done on a test cluster by the operator.  Please ask any clarifying
questions before you get started doing implementation work.  Can you implement this
feature?
